SUMMARY:Housing Justice Art Hang
DESCRIPTION:Join the Housing Justice Workgroup for an outing at the Frye Art Museum. This event is open to all DSA members\, whether you’re part of the housing justice workgroup or just looking to connect with comrades and enjoy the art exhibits. \nWe’ll gather from 11:00–11:15 AM in the Frye Parlor (just outside the café) before heading into the galleries together to explore\, connect\, and reflect on art through a shared lens of justice and solidarity. Join us then\, or drop in anytime between 11:00 AM and 1:00 PM and come find us in the galleries! \n✨ The first 15 DSA members to arrive will receive a DSA pin featuring our new logo. If you’re comfortable doing so\, we’ll ask you to wear it so others can easily spot the group as we move through the museum. Admission is free but we encourage you to make a donation to support the museum if you’re able. \nPublic street parking is available and free on Sundays along Terry Ave\, 9th Ave\, Columbia St\, Marion St\, and Cherry St.  \nFor public transit options\, accessibility details\, and museum policies\, please visit the Frye Art Museum website: https://fryemuseum.org. Bring a friend (or two)!
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/housing-justice-art-hang/
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA\, 98104\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts & Culture,Housing,New Member Friendly,Socials
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://seattledsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/DSA-Frye-Art-Museum-Day-3-scaled.png
GEO:47.6071321;-122.3241506
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Frye Art Museum 704 Terry Ave Seattle WA 98104 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=704 Terry Ave:geo:-122.3241506,47.6071321
END:VEVENT
