SUMMARY:Local Council Meeting
DESCRIPTION:The Local Council (LC) is the elected leadership body which serves the members of Seattle DSA. During these short weekly check-ins\, LC members will primarily be ensuring work is on track\, though pressing business may occasionally be discussed and voted on. Members are welcome to observe LC meetings\, which are held on the chapter’s Discord server. To join our Discord\, please visit https://seattledsa.org/join-discord/ and follow the instructions. Thereafter\, you will be able to observe LC meetings on the #lc-voice channel every Tuesday (except the fourth Tuesday of the month when we hold our monthly General Membership Meeting) from 7:00pm – 7:45pm over Zoom. \nIf there’s something specific you’d like to bring to the Local Council\, please fill out the LC Request Form which can be found on the private resources page of our website. \nPlease note that on rare occurrences\, LC meetings will be cancelled due to holidays or unusual circumstances and these changes may not always be reflected on this calendar — if you show up to the meeting and aren’t let in after 5 minutes\, that is almost certainly what has happened.
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/local-council-meeting-6-2-2/2026-05-05/
LOCATION:Online (Discord)
CATEGORIES:SDSA Local Council,SDSA Local Council Meeting
END:VEVENT
