UID:10018343-1778337000-1778342400@seattledsa.org
SUMMARY:New Labor Organizer Training
DESCRIPTION:RSVP HERE \nHave you ever… \n\nWanted more rights at work?\nWanted to fight back against the corporate class?\nBeen thinking “I need a union\,” but don’t know how to make it happen?\n\nThis workshop will teach you what you need to get started at your workplace! \nThis is intended for people at currently non-union workplaces who want to take the first steps toward organizing\, whether you want to join an existing union\, form a new one\, or organizing demands of your boss without a union at all. \nOur experienced labor organizers will teach you how to have an organizing conversation and how to form your Organizing Committee. \nWhen we organize\, we win! \n\nPLEASE NOTE: The Cathy Hillenbrand Community Room is NOT at Cal Anderson! Do not believe Google Maps!\nIt is at the corner of 10th Ave E & John St.\nThere will be a social to follow this event at Outer Planet Brewing!
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/new-labor-organizer-training/
LOCATION:Cathy Hillenbrand Community Room\, 923 E John St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98102\, United States
CATEGORIES:Education,Labor,New Member Friendly
ORGANIZER;CN="SDSA Labor Working Group":MAILTO:labor@seattledsa.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260509T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260509T160000
DTSTAMP:20260411T175016
CREATED:20260402T195156Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260402T195158Z
UID:10018344-1778337000-1778342400@seattledsa.org
SUMMARY:Build a Better Union panel discussion
DESCRIPTION:RSVP HERE \nIn some unions\, it’s tough to get involved beyond paying dues. Maybe leadership is an exclusive club or maybe they’re just checked out\, but something needs to change. Even when you can get involved\, is it a struggle? Are you really being listened to? Are your coworkers engaged with the union\, or just paper members? \nBuilding democratic participation makes a stronger\, fighting union. Come hear from union members who are currently organizing to do just that\, even when union leadership doesn’t agree with them. Learn how these members are working to build a better union from the inside\, and how you can apply their lessions to your own local. \nIf you are a current union staffer\, we ask that you not attend this event. Please join us afterwards at Outer Planet! \nThe Cathy Hillenbrand Community Room is NOT at Cal Anderson! Do not believe Google Maps!\nIt is at the corner of 10th Ave E & John St. \n\nThere will be a social to follow this event at Outer Planet Brewing!
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/build-a-better-union-panel-discussion/
LOCATION:Capitol Hill Branch Library\, 425 Harvard Ave E\, Seattle\, WA\, 98102\, United States
CATEGORIES:Education,Labor,New Member Friendly
ORGANIZER;CN="SDSA Labor Working Group":MAILTO:labor@seattledsa.org
GEO:47.6229294;-122.3223185
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Capitol Hill Branch Library 425 Harvard Ave E Seattle WA 98102 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=425 Harvard Ave E:geo:-122.3223185,47.6229294
END:VEVENT
